President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring September 9 to September 11 as National Days of Prayer and Remembrance in honor of the 10th anniversary of the September 11, 2001 terrorist attacks. The proclamation calls for the American people to honor and remember the victims of the attacks through prayer, contemplation, memorial services, visiting memorials, ringing bells, candlelight vigils, and other appropriate ceremonies and activities. The proclamation also recognizes the sacrifices made by the 9/11 Generation of service members and their families, as well as the efforts of first responders, law enforcement officials, diplomats, and others in building a safer world. President Obama invites people around the world to participate in this commemoration.